Install scripts of my Void+dwm linux rice
A short description of what it does:
* syncs home folder with github dotfiles repostiry
* disables tty3, tty4, ... and only leaves tty2
* changes tty1 to an auto-login tty
* disables grub os prober a changes the splash screen to Void logo
* allows user to run reboot, poweroff and shutdown without requiring password (it overwrites the sudoers file)
* syncs void repository and installs a list of programs from the 'programs' file through xbps-install or from my or others' forks on github
* symlinks user configs of bash, lf and vim to system-wide configs

